						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">What slider settings would produce a correct image for PAL?</div>
<br />
<br />artifacts = sqrt( -1 );
<br />
<br />Seriously, I now have a PAL NES motherboard (thanks to Eli Dayan) but haven't taken the time to get my devcart serial routines adjusted for its differing clock rate. I don't have a PAL TV, but my video capture works with it at full PAL resolution, so I'll investigate it at some point (along with the PAL APU). Based on preliminary inspection of the image, it appears that the PAL artifacts repeat every 6 or so scanlines. Some people claim that the artifacts in PAL are pretty much invisible; if this is the case, the S-Video setting should work (with perhaps a hue adjustment). Someone familiar with how a PAL NES looks could do some comparisons.</div>

